🧠 1. What is .map() (Super Simple)

.map() is a JavaScript function used to loop through an array and return something new.

👉 Think:
“Take list → transform each item → return new list”


---

🔹 Basic JS Example

const nums = [1, 2, 3];

const result = nums.map(n => n * 2);

console.log(result); // [2, 4, 6]


---

⚛️ 2. .map() in React (Core Idea)

In React, .map() is mainly used to: 👉 Display lists (UI rendering)


---

🔹 Example: Rendering List

export default function App() {
  const fruits = ["Apple", "Banana", "Mango"];

  return (
    <div>
      {fruits.map((fruit) => (
        <p>{fruit}</p>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

👉 Output:

Apple
Banana
Mango


---

⚠️ 3. Most Important Rule: key

React needs a unique key for each item.


---

❌ Wrong

{fruits.map(fruit => <p>{fruit}</p>)}

✅ Correct

{fruits.map((fruit, index) => (
  <p key={index}>{fruit}</p>
))}

👉 Better: use id instead of index (important for real apps)


---

🧩 4. Real Data (Objects Array)

export default function App() {
  const users = [
    { id: 1, name: "Adithya" },
    { id: 2, name: "Rahul" },
  ];

  return (
    <div>
      {users.map(user => (
        <p key={user.id}>{user.name}</p>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}


---

🔥 5. Add Styling / Components (Real Usage)

function UserCard({ name }) {
  return <h2>{name}</h2>;
}

export default function App() {
  const users = ["Adithya", "Rahul"];

  return (
    <div>
      {users.map((user, i) => (
        <UserCard key={i} name={user} />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

👉 This is how real apps are built.


---

⚡ 6. .map() + filter() (Very Important)

const nums = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];

{nums
  .filter(n => n % 2 === 0)
  .map(n => <p key={n}>{n}</p>)
}

👉 Output: 2, 4


---

🧠 7. Conditional Rendering inside .map()

{nums.map(n => (
  n % 2 === 0 ? <p key={n}>{n}</p> : null
))}


---

🚀 8. API Data (Real World Example)

import { useEffect, useState } from "react";

export default function App() {
  const [users, setUsers] = useState([]);

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users")
      .then(res => res.json())
      .then(data => setUsers(data));
  }, []);

  return (
    <div>
      {users.map(user => (
        <p key={user.id}>{user.name}</p>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}


