❌ 9. Common Mistakes (VERY IMPORTANT)

❌ Forgetting return

{nums.map(n => {
  <p>{n}</p>   // ❌ nothing returns
})}

✅ Fix

{nums.map(n => (
  <p>{n}</p>
))}


---

❌ Using .map() without array

const data = null;
data.map(...) // ❌ error

✅ Fix

{data?.map(...)}


---

🏁 10. Pro-Level Patterns

🔹 Nested .map()

const data = [
  { id: 1, items: ["A", "B"] },
];

{data.map(d => (
  <div key={d.id}>
    {d.items.map(item => (
      <p key={item}>{item}</p>
    ))}
  </div>
))}


---

🔹 Inline Arrow + Destructuring

{users.map(({ id, name }) => (
  <p key={id}>{name}</p>
))}


---

🎯 Final Cheat Sheet

.map() = loop + return UI

Always use key

Works on arrays only

Combine with filter()

Use components for clean code

Handle null with ?.



